         <abstract>
            <p>This record refers to the collection of prayers to the Trinity for each day of the week
               (<ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2296Sayfas">Sayfa Śǝllāse</ref>) together with miracles either following the prayer
            for each day one by one or following the prayers as a whole.</p>
            <p>This work is different from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2281Trinity">Taʾammǝra Śǝllāse</ref> (a collection of miracles of the Trinity attributed
               to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2748BeduaA">Bǝḍuʿa ʾAmlāk</persName>) and from
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2282Trinity">Taʾammǝra Śǝllāse</ref> (a collection of miracles of the 
               Trinity transmitted with <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1300Dersan">Dǝrsāna Śǝllāse</ref>).</p>
            <p>   From     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/CDVHURR9"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS"/><title level="a">Täʾammǝrä sǝllase</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Denis</forename><surname>Nosnitsin</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><editor><forename>Alessandro</forename><surname>Bausi</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2010</date><biblScope unit="volume">IV</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">975-976</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS</note></bibl> (minimally rephrased): A collection of miracles worked
            by the Trinity, in which
            a wondrous story follows a homily, for each
            day of the week. One of the types of the collections known as the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2388Taamme">Miracles of the Trinity</ref>
            </p>
         
         </abstract>
